            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Three pellets, about 0.2 cm in thickness and 20 mm in",
                "diameter, were formed by pressing approximately 10",
                "gram of CeO2 (99.99% pure) powder at 980 Mpa. The",
                "samples were irradiated in contact with the target",
                "and sandwiched between two standard Nb foils (99.99%",
                "pure, 0.5 mm thick) of the same diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were produced by the T(d,n)4He",
                "reaction with an effective deuteron beam energy of",
                "125 keV and beam current of 200 uA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A high-purity germanium detector, crystal",
                "diameter: 70.1 mm, crystal length: 72.3 mm, with a",
                "relative efficiency of about 68% and an energy",
                "resolution of 1.69 keV at 1.332 keV for 60Co. The",
                "detector was pre-calibrated for energy and efficiency",
                "by using the standard gamma ray sources 54Mn, 57Co,",
                "60Co, 109Cd, 133Ba, 137Cs, 152Eu, 241Am and 226Ra."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron flux was monitored by a uranium",
                "fission chamber allowing corrections to be made for",
                "small variations in the yield."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiation of the samples was lasted",
                "approximately 2 hours with a yield about 3 to",
                "4E10 n/(4pi*s). The groups of samples were placed at",
                "0, 90, and 135 degree relative to the beam direction",
                "and centered about a 2.40 mg/cm2 thick T-Ti target at",
                "a distance of about 5 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
